**MUST HAVES**
* 3\\+ years of experience with Python;
* 3\\+ years of experience in a Data Engineering role;
* Proficiency in programming languages commonly used in data engineering such as Python, SQL, and optionally Scala for working with data processing frameworks like Spark and libraries like Pandas;
* Proficiency in designing, deploying, and managing data pipelines using Apache Airflow for workflow orchestration and scheduling;
* Ability to design, develop, and optimize ETL processes to move and transform data from various sources into the data warehouse, ensuring data quality, reliability, and efficiency;
* Knowledge of big data technologies and frameworks such as Apache Spark for processing large volumes of data efficiently;
* Extensive hands\\-on experience with various AWS services relevant to data engineering, including Amazon MWAA, Amazon S3, Amazon RDS, Amazon EMR, AWS Lambda, AWS Glue, Amazon Redshift, AWS Data Pipeline, Amazon DynamoDB;
